The article is a readout of a briefing that President Obama received on Hurricane Sandy. The President convened a video-teleconference with his team to discuss the latest updates on the hurricane and the federal efforts to support response activities in New Jersey and New York. The President approved major disaster declarations for these states, allowing for additional federal support and assistance to affected individuals. The briefing included discussions on the track and impacts of the storm, federal coordination and resources, financial market conditions, and the need to provide resources to state and local responders quickly. The President emphasized the importance of restoring power and directed the Department of Defense and the Department of Energy to continue working with FEMA on this goal. The President urged Americans to follow the direction of local officials and remain focused on the response to Hurricane Sandy.